---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Vampire Crawlers Beginner\'s Guide — Tips & Getting Started (2026)';
const description = 'Complete beginner guide to Vampire Crawlers. Learn basics, combat, deckbuilding, early game strategy, and how to survive your first runs.';
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} canonical="https://vampcrawlers.cc/guides/beginners-guide">
  <article>
    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold text-white mb-1">Beginner's Guide</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-500 mb-6">Everything new players need — from first card to first victory.</p>

    <div class="toc">
      <div class="toc-title">Contents</div>
      <ol>
        <li><a href="#what-is">What Is Vampire Crawlers?</a></li>
        <li><a href="#basics">Getting Started: The Basics</a></li>
        <li><a href="#early-game">Early Game Strategy</a></li>
        <li><a href="#bloodfang">First Character: Bloodfang</a></li>
        <li><a href="#mistakes">Common Beginner Mistakes</a></li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <h2 id="what-is">What Is Vampire Crawlers?</h2>
    <p>Vampire Crawlers is a roguelike deckbuilder action game from <strong>poncle</strong> (creators of Vampire Survivors). Released April 2026, it merges card-based combat with bullet heaven survivor mechanics. You build a deck, fight through procedurally generated dungeons, and progressively unlock new cards, characters, and relics.</p>

    <div class="info-box">
      <strong>Key Difference from Vampire Survivors</strong>: In Vampire Crawlers, you actively play cards rather than relying on auto-attacks. This makes positioning, card timing, and deck management critical skills.
    </div>

    <h2 id="basics">Getting Started: The Basics</h2>

    <h3>1. Understanding Cards</h3>
    <p>Cards are your primary tool. Each card has:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Energy Cost</strong> — Playing a card costs energy. Energy regenerates over time.</li>
      <li><strong>Effect</strong> — Damage, healing, summon, buff, or debuff.</li>
      <li><strong>Element</strong> — Blood (lifesteal), Frost (freeze), Shadow (crit/burst), Lightning (AoE/speed).</li>
      <li><strong>Rarity</strong> — Common → Uncommon → Rare → Epic → Legendary.</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="tip-box">
      <strong>Pro Tip:</strong> Don't hoard cards. Play them as soon as you have energy — sitting at full energy is wasting resources.
    </div>

    <h3>2. Combat Flow</h3>
    <p>Combat is real-time. Enemies spawn in waves. Your deck cycles automatically — when empty, it reshuffles. Movement is essential:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Keep moving — standing still = dead in 3 seconds</li>
      <li>Watch for red telegraph indicators on enemy attacks</li>
      <li>Prioritize killing ranged enemies first</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>3. The Dungeon Crawl Loop</h3>
    <p>Each run goes through multiple floors. Between floors you can:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Pick new cards</strong> to expand your deck</li>
      <li><strong>Upgrade existing cards</strong> at the Forge (costs gold)</li>
      <li><strong>Heal</strong> at Blood Altars (costs gold)</li>
      <li><strong>Buy relics</strong> from the Merchant for permanent passive bonuses</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="warn-box">
      <strong>Warning:</strong> Blood Altars get more expensive each time you use them. Don't rely on them — build sustain into your deck instead.
    </div>

    <h2 id="early-game">Early Game Strategy</h2>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Start with Bloodfang.</strong> Balanced stats, self-healing passive — perfect for learning.</li>
      <li><strong>Prioritize AoE cards early.</strong> Clear groups of weak enemies fast.</li>
      <li><strong>Get one healing card by Floor 3.</strong> Vampiric Strike or Healing Light.</li>
      <li><strong>Don't skip relic rooms.</strong> Relics define your run. Always visit them.</li>
      <li><strong>Thin your deck.</strong> Remove weak starter cards at the Forge. Lean decks are consistent.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2 id="bloodfang">First Character: Bloodfang</h2>
    <div class="stat-grid mb-4">
      <div class="stat-item"><div class="stat-value">200</div><div class="stat-label">HP</div></div>
      <div class="stat-item"><div class="stat-value">5</div><div class="stat-label">Energy</div></div>
      <div class="stat-item"><div class="stat-value">3/5</div><div class="stat-label">Speed</div></div>
      <div class="stat-item"><div class="stat-value">Blood</div><div class="stat-label">Element</div></div>
    </div>
    <p><strong>Passive:</strong> Heal 2 HP every time you play a Blood card. Build around Blood cards for maximum sustain.</p>
    <p>Once you clear Floor 10, you unlock <strong>Frostveil</strong>.</p>

    <h2 id="mistakes">Common Beginner Mistakes</h2>
    <div class="danger-box">
      <strong>#1 Mistake:</strong> Taking every card offered. A lean 15-20 card deck is far stronger than a bloated 35-card deck.
    </div>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Ignoring relics</strong> — Relics are run-defining. Always visit relic rooms.</li>
      <li><strong>One-element obsession</strong> — Two elements cover each other's weaknesses.</li>
      <li><strong>Standing still</strong> — Movement is your best defense.</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 mt-8 pt-4 border-t border-gray-800 text-sm">
      <span class="text-gray-500">Next guides:</span>
      <a href="/guides/best-builds" class="text-red-400 hover:underline font-medium">Best Builds →</a>
      <a href="/guides/cards-tier-list" class="text-red-400 hover:underline font-medium">Cards Tier List →</a>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
